This paper focuses on community detection in online social networks, which involves analyzing the structure, content, and interactions within these networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of different weightings and types of communities, which could fall under cs.SD (Software Engineering) or cs.SOC (Social and Economic Networks). The paper also mentions analyzing topics, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.CL (Computation and Language).
